race.comment: CASH FOR KOTA (1) turned in a solid run last start over 300m at Taree Super Track finishing 4th and beaten only 3.5 lengths (17.94). Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. GREAT NORTH (7) has mixed form a little and missed the frame the last two but was a Grade 5 winner three back (22.80) at Maitland over 400m. Can find the frame this time. STOLE MY BONE (3) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 3 lengths at this track in a handy 19.43 beating Halo Grace. Goes well out of this box with a win and six minor placings. One of the key runners again. ZIP ZIPPITY ZIP (2) deserves plenty of thought at her first run at this circuit.
